Sunday, July 23, 2017




































Thomas Craig Obituary






Thomas Lester Craig Jr.MoultonFuneral service for Thomas Lester Craig Jr., 70, of Moulton will be Saturday, February 1, 2014, at 11 a.m. at Lawrence Funeral Home with Charles Williams officiating. Burial will be in Moulton Memory Gardens. Visitation will be tonight from 6 to 8 at the funeral home.Mr. Craig, who died Wednesday, January 29, 2014, at Northwest Medical Center, was born July 18, 1943, in Moulton to Thomas Lester Craig Sr. and Era Moore Craig. He was retired as a production worker for Decatur Aluminum. His parents preceded him in death.Survivors include two sons, Timothy B. Craig (Nancy) and Lewis Damon Craig (Annie), both of Moulton; one daughter, Emily Gravatt of Moulton; one brother, Roger Craig of Moulton; four sisters, Doris Sicso of Decatur, Elaine LouAllen of Moulton, Gaynell Henson of Tuscaloosa and Rhonda Hatton of Hatton; three grandsons, Bryan Craig, Brody Craig and Jesse Craig; four stepgrandchildren, Ivy Harris, Kheala Roberts, Daniel Neely and Steven Freeman; and two stepgreat-grandsons, Landon Freeman and Jax Freeman.Pallbearers will be nephews. This obituary was originally published in the Decatur Daily.				
				








